File: Former Social Development Minister Bathabile Dlamini. GCIS JOHANNESBURG - Former Social Development Minister Bathabile Dlamini's pension has been held. It is understood Sassa wants the money to go towards repaying for VIP protection services for Dlamini's family. READ: Bathabile Dlamini resigns from Parliament The agency has approached the court in an effort to recover just over R2-million from Dlamini and former CEO Virginia Petersen. Sassa also seeks the court's assistance in recovering just over R1.4-million from Petersen and former Social Development spokesperson Lumka Oliphant.